HB 196 Original 2026 Regular Session Beaullieu
Abstract: Increases number of personal leave days granted to certain teachers.
Sick Leave
Present law (R.S. 17:1201) provides every teacher employed by a parish or city school board
with 10 days of absence per school year for personal illness or because of other emergencies
or special circumstances, without loss of pay. Proposed law retains present law.
Personal Leave
Present law (R.S. 17:1208) authorizes every such teacher, except those who receive annual
leave, to take up to two days of personal leave every school year, which is deducted from
his 10 days of sick leave. Proposed law increases number of allowable days of personal
leave per school year from two to four.
(Amends R.S. 17:1208)
